IRS990.MissionDesc: A direct support organization for Miami Dade College (see Schedule O for additional information)
IRS990.Desc: The Foundation awarded numerous scholarships during the current year with a vast majority to students attending Miami Dade College. The remaining scholarships were awarded to graduates of the College for further studies at other colleges and universities.A significant number of scholarship recipients are considered low income and live below the federal poverty level.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The Foundation also supports donor funded facility projects, events, programs and cultural activities of the College such as the Miami Film Festival and Miami Book Fair.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990 governing body review Part VI line 11
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The BODs audit committee reviews the annual tax return form 990 prior to its issuance

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Conflict of interest policy compliance Part VI line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Secretary of the Board of Directors reviews annual disclosure statements to determine whether any conflict of interest exists among Trustees; if so the audit committee chair and executive committee members monitor such activity throughout the year.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: CEO executive director top management comp Part VI line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: College holds responsibility for salary recommendations for executive team members of the College

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Other officer or key employee compensation Part VI line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Compensation is reviewed and approved by the Board of Trustees after studies of compensation plans of like institutions

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Governing documents etc available to public Part VI line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Public notice is published for all Board meetings and minutes are available upon request

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part III response or note to any other line in Part III
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Description of the Organizations MissionMiami Dade College Foundation is a Florida Not-For-Profit corporation formed to serve as a direct support oranization, as defined in section 1004.70 of the Florida statues, of Miami Dade College, which is legally separate but financially accountable to the College.The Foundation was organized and operates exclusively to receive,hold,invest,and administer property and to make expenditures to,or for the benefit of the College including educational and cultural events.
